  "prompt": "What does 4 days late on my period mean?",
  "response": "If your period is 4 days late, it could be due to a variety of reasons. Here are a few possibilities:\n\n1. **Pregnancy**: A missed period is often one of the first signs of pregnancy. If you are sexually active, consider taking a home pregnancy test.\n\n2. **Stress**: High levels of stress can affect your menstrual cycle and cause a delay.\n\n3. **Changes in Weight**: Significant weight loss or gain can impact your hormones and menstrual cycle.\n\n4. **Travel or Changes in Routine**: Disruptions in your usual routine, such as traveling or changes in sleep patterns, can affect your cycle.\n\n5. **Illness**: Acute or chronic illness can affect your menstrual cycle.\n\n6. **Medications**: Certain medications, including birth control, can influence your cycle.\n\n7. **Hormonal Imbalances**: Conditions like polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) or thyroid issues can cause irregular periods.\n\n8. **Perimenopause**: If you are nearing menopause, your periods may become irregular.\n\nIf your period doesn\u2019t arrive in the next few days or if this becomes a recurring issue, it may be worth consulting a healthcare professional to rule out any underlying conditions.",
